T28.notes:
This table is based on place of enumeration.
Labour force status; Non-school qualifications - Applicable to persons aged 15 years and over.
Employed, worked full-time - 'Employed, worked full-time' is defined as having worked 35 hours or more in all jobs during the week prior to Census Night.
Employed, away from work - Comprises employed persons who did not work any hours in the week prior to Census Night or who did not state their number of hours worked.
% Unemployment - The number of unemployed persons expressed as a percentage of the total labour force.
% Labour force participation - The number of persons in the labour force expressed as a percentage of persons aged 15 years and over.
% Employment to population - The number of employed persons expressed as a percentage of persons aged 15 years and over.
Lived at same address 1 year ago; Lived at different address 1 year ago - Excludes persons less than 1 year of age.
Lived at same address 5 years ago; Lived at different address 5 years ago - Excludes persons less than 5 years of age.

(c) Includes families where at least one member aged 15 years and over did not state an income and/or was temporarily absent on Census Night and families where no persons stated an income and/or was temporarily absent on Census Night.
Both employed, full-time; One employed full-time; One employed full-time; Both employed, full-time; One employed full-time; One employed full-time; Employed full-time - 'Employed, worked full-time' is defined as having worked 35 hours or more in all jobs during the week prior to Census Night.
One employed, one away from work; One away from work; Both employed, away from work; One employed, one away from work; One away from work; Both employed, away from work - Comprises employed persons who did not work any hours in the week prior to Census Night or who did not state their number of hours worked.
One employed full-time(d), one not working; One employed part-time, one not working; One away from work(e), one not working; One employed full-time(d), one not working; One employed part-time, one not working; One away from work(e), one not working - Includes families where one partner was employed and the other was unemployed or not in the labour force.
Both not working; Both not working - Includes families where both partners were unemployed or not in the labour force, and families where one partner was unemployed and the other not in the labour force.
Labour force status not stated; Labour force status not stated; Labour force status not stated - Includes families where one or both parents/partners did not state his/her labour force status or a parent/partner was temporarily absent.
